# FEA SOLVER — PROJECT CONTEXT (claude.mb)
# Source of truth for all AI-assisted development.
# Updated: 2026-06-14 — audit fixes (001-008, 011) complete. 182 Python + 37 C# tests passing.

---

## OVERVIEW

Windows-native WPF desktop application wrapping CalculiX (FEA solver) and Gmsh (mesher).
Scope: 3D linear static structural analysis only.
Workflow: Import STEP → Mesh → Assign BCs/Loads → Run → Visualize results.

---

## TECHNOLOGY STACK

| Layer            | Technology                        | Reason                                                  |
|------------------|-----------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| UI               | WPF (.NET 8, C#)                 | Windows-native, mature, MVVM-friendly                   |
| 3D Viewport      | HelixToolkit.Wpf                 | OpenGL-backed, STEP/mesh display, hit-testing           |
| STEP Import      | OpenCascade (OCC via PythonOCC)  | Industry-standard STEP kernel; C# OCC bindings fragile  |
| Meshing          | Gmsh (Python API or CLI)         | Best-in-class open-source tet mesher; Python API clean  |
| FEA Solver       | CalculiX (ccx.exe)               | Open-source, *.inp/*.frd format, well-documented        |
| Parsing/Scripts  | Python 3.11+                     | Gmsh API, OCC, FRD parsing, mesh I/O                    |
| C#/Python IPC    | File-based + subprocess          | Simple, debuggable, no COM/gRPC complexity              |
| Config           | appsettings.json (C#)            | Standard .NET config, no hardcoded paths                |
| Logging          | Serilog (C#) + Python logging    | Structured logs, file sink                             |
| Units            | SI throughout (m, Pa, N)         | Consistent; UI displays mm/MPa with conversion         |

