## EXTENSIBILITY HOOKS

| Feature | Where to extend |
|---------|-----------------|
| Multiple materials | FEAModel.Materials[], INP writer per-ELSET |
| Multiple load cases | FEAModel.LoadCases[], *STEP iteration in INP |
| Modal analysis | New SolverMode enum → *FREQUENCY step |
| Nonlinear | *NLGEOM flag + *STATIC with increments |
| Thermal loads | *TEMPERATURE + *EXPANSION in INP |
| Remote force | Resolve to RBE2/RBE3 equivalent via MPC |
| Result types | Extend parse_frd.py for PE (plastic strain), etc. |

---

## SECURITY

- All subprocess calls use explicit executable paths from config (no shell=True in Python, UseShellExecute=false in C#).
- Work directory path constructed with Path.Combine, never string concat with user input.
- STEP file path validated (extension check, path traversal check) before passing to scripts.
- No eval(), no dynamic imports.

